sentences: Synne Skouen (born 8 August 1950) is a Norwegian music writer and composer.
She also studied with Finn Mortensen in Oslo receiving her degree in composition from the Norwegian Academy of Music in 1976.
Skouen appeared in the 1966 film Reisen til havet, directed by her father, Arne Skouen.
From 1977 to 1986 she worked as editor of the contemporary music periodical Ballade, and wrote as a music critic for Arbeiderbladet.
In 1993 Skouen became the music director for Norwegian Broadcasting's cultural channel, and in 1999 was named Head of Culture.
